                  <p>
                    Kate’s energetic personality and enthusiasm create an exciting and engaging therapy environment. She believes that developing close relationships with clients and families is an important aspect of successful speech/language therapy. Kate loves collaborating with other professionals to expand her practice.
                  </p>

                  <p>
                    Kate’s has professional experience in public schools. She has evaluated and treated children ranging from 3 to 16 years old and has worked with students diagnosed with articulation/phonological disorders, pragmatic language disorder, expressive/receptive language delay, emotional impairment,  Autism Spectrum Disorder, and Down Syndrome, among others.
                  </p>

                  <p>
                    Kate graduated from the University of Connecticut with a Bachelor of Arts degree in Speech, Language, and Hearing Sciences. She received a Master of Science degree in Speech-Language Pathology from Adelphi University in 2015. Kate is a certified member of the American Language Hearing Association (ASHA) and is trained in Picture Exchange Communication System (PECS).
                  </p>

                  <p>
                    Kate is recently engaged, and moved to Boston from Connecticut and enjoys exploring her new city as well as watching movies, sports, and traveling.
                  </p>

